radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated to a maximum of 10 mm with trace surrounding fat stranding. Heart size is normal, lung bases are clear, liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesion, gallbladder is unremarkable, and kidneys present symmetric nephrograms without focal lesion. No free air, no ascites or pneumoperitoneum, and small fat-containing umbilical hernia.
